These are the steps:

1) run_create_topo.tx2_3v3.pbs (qsub run_create_topo.tx2_3v3.pbs)
Creates basic topography file with raw cell level depth statistics and a first cut mask
output = topo.sub150.tx2_3v3.SRTM15_V2.4.nc

2) MaskEdit_tx2_3v3.ipynb
Edits land mask including now removing 1-point bays around Greenland and Antarctica
output = topo.sub150.tx2_3v3.SRTM15_V2.4.edit1.nc

3) run_append_topo_interp_smooth_tx2_3v3.pbs (qsub run_append_topo_interp_smooth_tx2_3v3.pbs)
Appends a new depth variable D_interp to the topography file with lightly smoothed depths

4) Append_topo_edits_tx2_3v3.ipynb
Hand edits depths for straits and channels. This creates the model input file. The final topography variable (model input) is called D_edit2

6) Channel_width_tx2_3v3.ipynb
create channel width file

Optional (not used in v3)

7) Channel_topo_tx2_3v3.ipynb
local topography depth edits for run time changes

If changes in 7) must be incorporated into the topography generated in 3), run the following notebook

8) Append_topo_edits.ipynb


There are a couple of notebooks in the source directory for checking things as you go along:

1. CompareFirstMasks.ipynb : make sure step 1 reproduces tx2_3v2 data
2. CompareEditedMasks.ipynb : check mask after step 2 to make sure only changes are as intended
3. CheckRunoffPoints.ipynb : same thing with focus on places we meant to change
4. CompareDepths.ipynb : compare the final depths from step 4 above to make sure they agree with both the input and output files from tx2_3v2 - should only see depth differences for the 30 points we filled in tx2_3v3. Note there are roundoff level differences in the depths (O(10^-3 m)) from tx2_3v2, maybe because of the new grid file.
